'''Bryophyta''' ({{IPAc-en|,|b|r|aɪ|oʊ|'|f|aɪ|t|ə}}, {{respell|BRY|oh|FY|tə}}), the Moss Giantess, is a [[moss giant]] [[boss]] who can be found in her lair in the [[Varrock Sewers]]. The entrance to the lair is located just east of the moss giants in the sewers, and can be accessed by navigating the sewers, using the level 51 [[Obstacle pipe (Edgeville Dungeon)|Agility shortcut]] from [[Edgeville Dungeon]], or by teleporting with a [[giantsoul amulet]].

A [[mossy key]] is needed to unlock the [[Gate (Bryophyta)|gate]] leading to Bryophyta's lair for the first time, but subsequent access to the lair does not require a key. The key will not be consumed when unlocking Bryophyta's lair.

The keys also open the [[Chest (Bryophyta's Lair)|chest]] found in her lair. Each opening uses one mossy key and requires one Bryophyta kill, similar to [[Obor]] and [[giant key]]s. Bryophyta respawns 15 ticks (9 seconds) after attempting to open her chest, or on leaving and re-entering the instance, regardless of whether the player has a mossy key in their inventory.

The chest is the sole source of [[Bryophyta's essence]], which is used to make [[Bryophyta's staff]]. This item can store [[nature rune]]s, and has a chance to not consume them when casting a spell that uses them.  

