==Strategy==
To access Bryophyta's lair, players will need a [[knife]] or a [[Slash weapons|slash weapon]] to cut through the web if approaching via the [[Varrock Sewers]]. Members with level 51 [[Agility]] can bypass this by using the agility [[shortcut]] near [[Vannaka]] in the [[Edgeville Dungeon]]. Alternatively, a charged [[Giantsoul amulet]] can teleport players directly outside the entrance to her lair.

Unlike Obor’s chambers, where he is confined in a small pit, players are taken directly to Bryophyta’s chambers, where she attacks on sight. It is recommended to activate [[Protect from Magic]] before entering, or immediately upon entry, before opening the [[Gate (Bryophyta)|gate]].

[[File:Fighting Bryophyta.png|thumb|left|250px|A player fighting Bryophyta.]]

In members' worlds, Bryophyta can [[poison]] players, starting at 8 damage. It is advisable to bring poison protection, as she ignores protection prayers.

During the fight, Bryophyta may summon three [[growthling]]s. While they are weak, they must be killed because Bryophyta is immune to all damage (except poison and venom) while they are alive. To kill them, they must be attacked with a '''woodcutting''' [[axe]] or [[magic secateurs]], one-shotting the growthlings. Although the [[blessed axe]] is a woodcutting axe, it will not work. If no item with the "[[Axe]]" attack type is brought, players can take a [[bronze axe]] from the [[logs (Bryophyta)|pile of logs]] in the lair; other types of axes, such as [[battleaxe]]s or the [[zombie axe]], '''cannot''' be used to kill the growthlings. Bryophyta can only summon one batch of growthlings at a time, and there is a cooldown between summons.

[[Free-to-play]] players should wear [[green d'hide armour]] for magic defence, along with a [[rune kiteshield]] and [[rune full helm]] for optimal protection against her attacks. God armours like [[Guthix armour]] offer a slight advantage with a +1 prayer bonus per piece and are only marginally more expensive than rune armour. Offensively, a [[rune scimitar]] is recommended for its strength bonus. Players should have at least 50 strength, attack, and defence before attempting to fight Bryophyta.

Ranging Bryophyta is the best strategy for mid-level F2P players, with recommended stats of 60 ranged, 40 defence, and 37 prayer. The ideal setup includes [[green d'hide armour]], a [[coif]], an [[amulet of power]], and a [[maple shortbow]] with [[adamant arrows]]. Maintaining a safe distance is crucial, as she won’t move towards players and won’t use melee attacks if they are out of her reach. Using [[Protect from Magic]] will further minimise damage. 

Bryophyta's 50% fire weakness makes magic highly viable in F2P. With at least 37 prayer and 59 magic, using Protect from Magic and Fire Blast offers the highest DPS for F2P players by a wide margin. As with the ranged strategy, keeping your distance is crucial. Best-in-slot magic gear with the Fire Staff is the recommended equipment.

