==Trivia==
*{{Wp|Bryophyta}} is the scientific name for mosses.
*The update which introduced Bryophyta also made [[Antipoison]] potions available to free-to-play players and able to be purchased from the [[Apothecary]] in Varrock.
**The idea of Bryophyta poisoning in free-to-play was scrapped prior to release; however, [[Antipoison]] potions still remain free-to-play.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1231689392995078146|date=23 February 2020|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/96770|archivedate=28 February 2020|quote=Not sure. The development of that particular boss was difficult, due to the dev being very inexperienced at the time, with Maz having to step in very late on to take over. The original dev may have enabled them on F2P for a reason that was later scrapped.}}
*It is possible to have growthlings summoned at the same time Bryophyta gets last damage (even without poison or venom) and fight them after her death.
*As the axe is being used as a weapon and not as a tool, the player can still kill growthlings with an axe with a higher [[Woodcutting]] requirement than the player has.

